# act configuration — see CLAUDE.md "Testing workflows locally with `act`".
#
# Pin `ubuntu-latest` to catthehacker's image (Ubuntu 24.04-based, matches
# GitHub's current `ubuntu-latest` runner). The act default image is intentionally
# minimal and silently breaks Node/pnpm setups.
#
# Architecture is deliberately NOT pinned — act defaults to the host arch. On
# Apple Silicon that's arm64 (fast, native). To strictly mirror real
# `ubuntu-latest` (amd64) for parity debugging, append
# `--container-architecture linux/amd64` to the command.
-P ubuntu-latest=catthehacker/ubuntu:act-latest
